The phrase '''Kicking the habit''' can be used in many contexts, ranging from comical to serious, to mean recovering or quitting from an addiction or habit. It is used in encouragement for stopping or quitting all habits from smoking, drinking and burping, to alcohol and drug addiction.

It comes from when a hard drug addict, usually a heroin addict, involuntarily moves their legs in a kicking motion during the withdrawal stage from the drug, and normally happens while the addict is in bed.